== 1...Na6?! · Lemming defence ==

A rare and weak response to 1. e4. The knight develops to a square that doesn't control the centre and as such, it's a wasted opportunity. 

This allows White to take the full centre with '''2. d4'''. The most serious line is 2...c6, which transposes to the [[Chess Opening Theory/1. e4/1...c6/2. d4/2...Na6|De Bruycker line of the Caro-Kann defence]]. 2...c5!? (defended by the knight on the rim) 3. Nf3 cxd4 leads to an unusual sort of Sicilian. 

=== History ===
The name "Lemming" comes from Eric Schiller.<ref>{{cite book  | author=Eric Schiller | year=2002 | edition=2nd | title=Unorthodox Chess Openings  | publisher=Cardoza  | isbn=1-58042-072-9 }}p.&nbsp;302</ref>

